{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Documentation Consistency Check",
  "description": "Scans all markdown files, AGENTS.md, README.md, and .kiro/* files for terminology drift and architectural inconsistencies. Automatically updates any inconsistencies found.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Execute documentation consistency check:\n\n1. Check recent git commits for context on terminology changes\n\n2. Identify canonical sources for this project/workspace:\n   - .kiro/specs/* (requirements.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n   - AGENTS.md (project steering at repo root)\n   - README.md (project overview)\n\n3. Search ALL markdown files recursively for drift in:\n   - Terminology (compare against canonical sources)\n   - Architecture descriptions (validate against .kiro/specs/*/design.md)\n   - Feature descriptions (validate against .kiro/specs/*/requirements.md)\n   - Cross-references between files\n\n4. Focus on these critical files:\n   - .kiro/* (all files, use ls -a)\n   - ALL AGENTS.md files (recursive search)\n   - ALL README.md files (recursive search)\n   - Code files with docstrings/comments\n\n5. Report findings:\n   - Files with outdated terminology\n   - Specific lines needing updates\n   - Suggested replacements based on canonical sources\n   - Overall consistency status\n\n6. Automatically fix ALL inconsistencies found. Final-state surgery: remove old terminology entirely, update all references to match canonical sources. Leave no trace. ðŸš®\n\nUNKNOWN > INVENTED. If terminology is ambiguous, ask before changing."
  },
  "workspaceFolderName": ".context",
  "shortName": "doc-consistency-check"
}